{"name": "ichingpy", "metadata": {"name": "ichingpy", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pydantic"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1735907249}, "documentation": ["# I-Ching Python\n\n## Description\nI-Ching Python is a fully object-oriented Python library for working with the I-Ching, an ancient Chinese divination text. \nThis library provides tools for \n1. generating hexagrams using multiple methods, \n2. interpreting their meanings   (TODO)\n3. performing divination based on the I-Ching (TODO)\n4. arithmetic operations on Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches (\u5e72\u652f)\n\n\n## Installation\n\n> pip install ichingpy\n\n## Quick Start\n\n\n```python\nimport ichingpy as icp\n```\n\nCreate a Line  (\u723b)\n```python\nyin = icp.Line(status=icp.LineStatus.CHANGING)\n```\n\nCreate a Trigram (\u516b\u5366)\n```python\nqian = icp.Trigram.from_binary([1, 1, 1])\n```\n\n\nCreate a Hexagram with transformation (\u53d8\u5366)\n```python\nqian_tai = icp.Hexagram.from_binary([3, 3, 3, 1, 1, 1]) # \u4e7e\u4e4b\u6cf0\n```\n\nA Hexagram can be also generated by using 50 yarrow stalks or 3 coins\n```python \nhexagram = icp.Hexagram.from_three_coins()\n\n```\n```python \nhexagram = icp.Hexagram.from_yarrow_stalks()\n```\n\n```\n-- --\n-- --\n-- --\n----- O -> -- --\n-- --\n----- O -> -- --\n```\n\nAssign HeavenlyStems to a hexagram\n```python\nfrom ichingpy.calculator.assigner import HexagramAssigner\nhexagram = icp.Hexagram.from_yarrow_stalks()\nassigner = HexagramAssigner()\nassigner.assign_stems(hexagram)\nhexagram.inner.stem\n```\n```\n[<HeavenlyStem.Ji: 6>, <HeavenlyStem.Ji: 6>, <HeavenlyStem.Ji: 6>]\n```\n\n#### Arithmetic operations on Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches (\u5e72\u652f)\n\n```python\n>>> icp.HeavenlyStem.Jia + 1\n<HeavenlyStem.Yi: 2>\n\n>>> gui = icp.HeavenlyStem.Gui\n>>> jia = icp.HeavenlyStem.Jia\n>>> jia + gui \n<HeavenlyStem.Jia: 1>\n```\n```python\n>>> jia = icp.HeavenlyStem.Jia \n>>> zi = icp.EarthlyBranch.Zi\n>>> jia_zi = icp.SexagenaryCycle(jia, zi)\n>>> jia_zi\n\u7532\u5b50\n>>> jia_zi+1\n\u4e59\u4e11\n>>> jia_zi+60\n\u7532\u5b50\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ichingpy", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ichingpy.EarthlyBranch", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.EarthlyBranch", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.HeavenlyStem", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.HeavenlyStem", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.Hexagram", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.Hexagram", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.Line", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.Line", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.LineStatus", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.LineStatus", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.SexagenaryCycle", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.SexagenaryCycle", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.Trigram", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.Trigram", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ichingpy.calculator", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ichingpy.model", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ichingpy.model.Hexagram", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.model.hexagram.Hexagram", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.model.Line", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.model.line.Line", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.model.SexagenaryCycle", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.model.sexagenary_cycle.SexagenaryCycle", "project": null}}, {"name": "ichingpy.model.Trigram", "xref": {"fqname": "ichingpy.model.trigram.Trigram", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ichingpy.calculator.assigner", "documentation": ["%%"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ichingpy.calculator.assigner.HexagramAssigner", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "ichingpy.calculator.assigner.HexagramAssigner.assign", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "hexagram", "type": {"na